<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" style="">{!Claim__c.Name}</font></span><div style=""><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></div><div style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Hello,</font><p style=""></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><font style="">We received your request to review disputed charges and have assigned the above claim number for card ending&nbsp;</font><font color="#000000">{!Claim__c.Abbreviated_Card__c}<font color="#330033">.</font></font><font style="">&nbsp;</font>We have received your claim and have begun our investigation.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">If you have not already done so, we suggest that a police report be filed and the stations involved be contacted immediately to obtain possible video surveillance evidence as most stations keep surveillance tape for only a short period of time.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">We require additional information in order to proceed with the review of your claim.&nbsp; Please submit the following items:</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""></p><ul style=""><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The full card number(s) that is in dispute.</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">A copy of the card(s)</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;</span><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">A copy of the Police Report</span></font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The date range of the disputed transactions.</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">The completion of the attached affidavit.<span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">Please ensure the following steps are completed:</span><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">&nbsp;</span></font></li><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Fully complete&nbsp;<u style="text-indent: -0.25in;">each</u><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">&nbsp;section and include card numbers.</span><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">&nbsp;</span></font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;">&nbsp;</span><span style="text-indent: -0.25in;">Sign and date the affidavit.</span></font></li></ul></ul><ul style=""><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">A detailed summary of why the transactions are being disputed including;</font></li><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">where the card(s) was kept prior to the abuse,</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">the circumstance around how the card(s) became lost or stolen, and</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">how the din(s) used would have been known.</font></li></ul></ul><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">You can return the documentation by fax: 207-791-1655, or email:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:disputes@fleetfraudservices.com">disputes@fleetfraudservices.com</a>&nbsp;, or mail to:</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="text-align: justify;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>Fleet Fraud Services</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="text-align: justify;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>97 Darling Avenue</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="text-align: justify;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>South Portland, ME 04106</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><b><i><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Please return the requested documentation within&nbsp;<u>10 business days</u>&nbsp;from the date of this letter. If the requested information is not received during the 10 business day time period your claim will be closed without further notification.<o:p></o:p></font></i></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNoSpacing" style=""><i><font face="Arial, sans-serif">If you currently do not have authorization controls assigned to your cards, we strongly encourage you to do so via your online account.&nbsp; If you need assistance with adding these controls, please contact Customer Service. In addition to the transactions currently being disputed, we also suggest that you review your account activity online. (The online account can be accessed through the web address located on the back of your billing statement and Customer Service is available for online assistance with this process.<o:p></o:p></font></i></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Please also understand that the company is obligated to keep the account current per the terms and conditions of the Agreement.&nbsp; Any credit due will be granted at the resolution of the claim. &nbsp;As we realize that this may create a hardship for your business, we are interested in working with you through this process.&nbsp; Should you need to discuss alternate payment options/arrangements, please contact:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:forbearance@fleetservicesonline.com" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">forbearance@fleetservicesonline.com</a>.&nbsp;<i>Please note that subject to any limitations imposed by&nbsp;applicable law, you may be liable to us for all unauthorized use of a card until you notify us of such use.</i><o:p></o:p></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><o:p><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif">While in most instances it may take significantly less time,&nbsp;<b><span style="background: yellow;">please allow us up to 90 days to resolve your claim</span></b>. &nbsp;We will contact you if additional information is required.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="Arial, sans-serif" style=""><br>Regards,</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Lucida Calligraphy&quot;; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Fleet Fraud Services<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);"><font size="2" style="" face="Arial, sans-serif">Fax: 207-791-1655</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font size="2" style="" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Email:&nbsp;</span>disputes@fleetfraudservices.com</font></p></div>]]></td>
